Swap the single `<div className="kanban-column-empty">No issues</div>` node in `apps/desktop/src/components/kanban/KanbanColumn.tsx` for an inline-SVG + label pair styled to match the v0.6.0 `DetailEmptyState` pattern, and update `kanban.css` so the empty state is centered, low-opacity, and uses design tokens.

### JSX (`KanbanColumn.tsx`, replacing the empty-branch at line ~56)

When the column is empty AND not currently a drop target (so the amber drop-target ring isn't fighting the illustration), render:

```tsx
{issues.length === 0 && !isOver && (
  <div className="kanban-column-empty">
    <svg
      className="kanban-column-empty-icon"
      width="28"
      height="28"
      viewBox="0 0 24 24"
      fill="none"
      stroke="currentColor"
      strokeWidth="1.5"
      strokeLinecap="round"
      strokeLinejoin="round"
      aria-hidden="true"
    >
      {/* Empty-tray glyph: outer tray + inner divider line */}
      <path d="M22 12h-6l-2 3h-4l-2-3H2" />
      <path d="M5.45 5.11 2 12v6a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h16a2 2 0 0 0 2-2v-6l-3.45-6.89A2 2 0 0 0 16.76 4H7.24a2 2 0 0 0-1.79 1.11z" />
    </svg>
    <span className="kanban-column-empty-label">No issues</span>
  </div>
)}
```

When `isOver` is true the empty branch renders `null` — the existing `.kanban-column--drop-target` amber inset ring on the column body remains the sole drop-target signal, no visual competition.

### CSS — `kanban.css` (replacing the existing `.kanban-column-empty` block, lines ~118–126)

```css
.kanban-column-empty {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  gap: 8px;
  height: 100%;
  min-height: 96px;
  padding: 16px 8px;
  color: var(--text-tertiary);
  opacity: 0.5;
  user-select: none;
}

.kanban-column-empty-icon {
  flex-shrink: 0;
  color: var(--text-tertiary);
}

.kanban-column-empty-label {
  font-size: 11px;
  line-height: 1;
  color: var(--text-tertiary);
  letter-spacing: 0.01em;
}
```

Keep the existing `.kanban-column--drop-target .kanban-column-body` amber-ring rule unchanged.

### Scope boundaries

- Two files only: `KanbanColumn.tsx` + `kanban.css`.
- Pure frontend, no Rust / IPC / state-shape changes.
- No new component file — markup is ~10 lines and stays inline.
- No motion / animation — issue and review both call for a static glyph; `prefers-reduced-motion` block in `kanban.css` already covers the column without expansion.
- Tokens only: `var(--text-tertiary)` for both icon stroke (via `currentColor` inheritance) and the label. Both themes adapt automatically — light theme's `--text-tertiary` is `#8b8b8b` against `#f3f3f3 ` body, dark theme's is `#6e7681` against `#252526`.

### Test plan

- `pnpm build` — clean tsc -b + vite production build.
- `pnpm test` — existing vitest suite green (no kanban-column test exists today; a snapshot test is not warranted for a 30-line visual change — manual verify suffices, consistent with how v0.6.0's #176 illustrated detail empty state shipped without a dedicated snapshot test).
- Manual smoke (developer): open the app, find a Kanban view with at least one empty column, verify the soft glyph + label render at ~50% opacity, are vertically centered, and disappear cleanly when a card is dragged over the column.
